===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{Han compound|禾|人|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=wheat; grain}}. Originally meaning "harvest", it later came to mean "year". In the oracle bone script and early bronze inscriptions, it was originally written like {{och-l|*秂}}.

In bronze inscriptions after the {{w|Western Zhou}} period, a stroke was often added to {{och-l|*人}} to give {{och-l|千}}, which still acted as a phonetic component, thus getting ({{och-l|*秊}}). The current form is inherited from the clerical script, where ''{{w|libian}}'' ({{zh-l|*隸變}}) has occurred.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-ni(ŋ~k)||year}}.

